"explanation": "The defendant was convicted of embezzling $25,000 from their employer, which constitutes a significant breach of fiduciary duty. However, as a first-time offender with no prior criminal record, the defendant shows a higher potential for rehabilitation. The fact that the money has been partially paid back demonstrates a degree of remorse and accountability. The outburst by the spectator has been entirely disregarded, as sentencing must be based on the law and facts of the case rather than public sentiment. Balanced against the gravity of the theft, a moderate period of incarceration is warranted to serve as a deterrent while acknowledging the mitigating factors of restitution and clean history.",
